    "description": "Mari and the Black Tower, known as <i>The Black Dungeon</i> on other platforms, is a jRPG featuring enhanced turn-based side-view combat.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Main Features</h2><br>●Four party members with eight unique classes, such as the Knight, Horn Artist and Bloodbinder, to choose from<br>●Classic turn-based combat enhanced with Instant abilities and an engaging TP system<br>●10 unique floors to climb and 30 quests to complete<br>●Hundreds of items, weapons and armors to find<br>●3 Difficulty modes--play on Easy for a casual experience or Hard to ramp the difficulty and give bosses new abilities<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Story</h2><br>Monsters and plagues pour out of the mysterious Black Tower. Forest nymph Mari and her partner, a young amnesiac named Abbie, must gather a band of heroes to scale the tower and uncover its secrets as it threatens to end all life on earth.<br><br><i>Mari and the Black Tower</i> is a stand-alone game and the third entry in the <i>Knights of Ambrose Saga.</i><br><br>---<br>An updated version of the game, re-titled <i><strong>The Black Dungeon,</strong></i>, is available on the Google Play Store. Mari and the Black Tower was inspired by underground jRPG classics such as <i>Guardian's Crusade</i> and <i>King's Field. </i>",
